{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_alastor_ver02/data/sn78003992/00340580928/1945082401/0293.xml":{"full_text":"Salvage of Goodyear\nAircraft Plants Is\nPart of Program\n(Continued from Page One)\nand present regulations prevent them\nfrom being used by Goodyear Air\ncraft Corporation to manufacture\nother products in direct competition\nwith other industry.\nIt is pointed out, however, that the\nGoodyear Aircraft Corporation might\ndiuolve itself and an, entirely new\ncorporation formed that will purchase\nthp buildings from the government\nand go into the manufacture of pre\nfabricated houses or other peacetime\nproducts.\nA resolution directed to Congress\nmen Huber and other members of\nCongress will be considered at the\nmeeting tonight in a move to make it\npossible for Goodyear Aircraft Corpo\nration to engage in other peacetime\nmanufacturing in the event the corpo-,\nration is Hot dissolved.\n\u2022The move to return to the shorter\nwork-week in Akron as the means of\npreventing a maximum amount of un\nemployment already has taken long\nstrides forward. The Goodrich man\nagement has agreed to the plan and\nGoodyear Local has approved a reso*\nRailroad\n(Continued from Page 1)\nare used jn this service, then the win\ndows should be opened, except on those\ncars where the window guides have\nbeen modified so that the windows can\nnot be opened, and (he pump and blow\ner mbtor fuses .should be removed so\nthat energy will not be taken from the\nbattery by the operation of these units.\n\"When the pump motor fuses and\nblower motor fuses are removed, the\nclips should be properly tagged to pre\nvent replacement while in troop move\nment during the cooling season.' Please\nbe governed accordingly.\u201d\nThe names of those officials to whom\nthe o^der was directed and their juris\ndication are as follows:\n(L.E.'M.), Lee E. Miller, Foremali,\nBack Shop, Fort Wayne, Indiana.\n(C.R.A.) C. R. Aiken, Foreman, En\ngine House, Fort Wayne, Indiana.\n(E.R.R.) E. R. Rouch, Foreman, En\ngine House, Fort Wayne, Indiana.\n(G.L.B.) G. L. Burris, Foreman, En\ngine House, Crestline, Ohio.\n(E.F.I..) E. F. Linn, Foreman, Car\nShop, Creslline, Ohio.\n(A.R.M.) A. R. Monroe, Foreman,\nCar Shop, Grand Rapids, Michigan.\nThe name of the official who issued\nthe order, and whose initials signed the\norder, is: (J.E.B.) J, E. Brower, Master\nMechanic,. Fort Wayne, Indiana.\nSunset and evening star,\nAnd one clear call for mel\nAnd may there be no nioatpng at\nthe bar,\nWhen I put out to sea.\n\u2014Tennyson.\n\"One is nearer God\u2019s heart in a\ngarden then any where on earth.\u201d\nlution asking management ol' that\ncompany to follow the Goodrich plan.\nIt is pointed out that several thousand\nmen and women will be retained on\nthe payrolls of the two companicJ if\nthe present 48-hour week is discarded.\nThe Goodyear resolution also sug\ngests an approximate 30 per cent in\ncrease in the basis pay rates in order\nthat the take-home pay of workers\nwill be almost the same as in the 48\nhour week. They point out that re\nduction in the amount of take-home\npay will result in lower purchasing\npower, which in turn will retard re\nconversion and economic stability.\nThe meeting of the Council Friday\nnight will be the first session of the\norganization since the surrender of\nJapan was announced officially by\nPresident Truman 10 days ago. All\nphases of the reconversion problem\nwill be discussed. A record-breaking\nnumber of delegates is expected to at\ntend the meeting because of the im\nportance of matters to be discussed.\nLABOR AIDS\nIN RELIEF I\n(Continued from Pave li\neight hostels and four medical clinics\nfor the use of industrial workers. <The\nfour clinics are attached to hostels.\nThese clinics have become famous and\nas recently as April 7,1945, received no\ntice in a repftrt written by Benjamin H.\nKizer, director of the China office of\nUNRRA. It is proposed to use China\u2019s\nallotment for building new hostels and\nmaintenance of those already in exis\ntence.\nHere is the amount Labor's War Re\nlief Program will spend in each coun\ntry:\nBelgium\u2014$200,000; an increase of\n$50,000 over last year.\nChina\u2014$700,000.\nCzechoslovakia\u2014$200,000.\nFrance\u2014$450,000; an increase of\n$150,000 over last year.\nItaly\u2014$200,000; an increase of $25,\n000 over last year.\nLuxembourg\u2014$25,000.\nPalestine\u2014$100,000.\nThe Philippines\u2014$100,000.\nPoland\u2014$250,000.\nNorway\u2014$125,000.\nHolland\u2014$250,000; an increase of\n$50,000 over last year.\nThe Union Label stands for libera\ntion from slave wages.\nHollywood Princess\nWardrobe Cabinet\n68-in. x 40-in. x 21%-in.\nCut a neat corner with E-Z Do\u2019s Hollywood\nPrincess wardrobe! Points of interest are the\n3-ply Kraftwood and wooden frames, eye\nlevel mirrors on both doors, and 2 removable\nshoes shelves. This gay washable plastic\ncoated cabinet holds 15 garments.\nPOLSKY HOUSEWARES-FIRST FLOOR.\nHomemakers, There's a 10-Year Guarantee On This\nSUPREME SST FURNACE\nFree healing estimate\nby O\u2019Neil\u2019s Heating\nExperts if you dial\nBL-1131.\n\n89\nMassive 1 -Pc.\nRadiator\nExtra-size Combustion\nDime\nEasy-shake Duplex 4\nGrates\nExtra Roomy, Deep\nAsh Pit ,i\nNow when yon no longer need\nheat' is the time to plan ahead\n--to get your home set for\nnext winter\u2019s cold apell with a\ndependable furnace. This su\npreme has been constructed to our\nexact specifications by one of the\nnation\u2019s three largest furnace mak\ners. It will give you dependable,\nmaximum long-life comfort and\nservice this Vinter and for many\nwinters to come. 1\nFURNACES\u2014FOURTH FLOOR\nThe M. O\u2019NEIL Company\n10 Point Reconversion\nProgram Offered by\nAFL Executives\n(Continued from Page' 1)\n\n8. Halt farther inductions into armed\nforces.\n9. Bring service men and women now\noverseas home as quickly as possible.\n10. Encourage the laun'qfaing of a\nhew housing program and all other\nmeasures which would reduce the dan\nger of widespread unemployment.\nAFL- President William Green said:\n\u201cWar contracts are being cancelled\nall over the nation. Factories are shut\nting down. Unemployment is bound to\nbecome serious. Some government\nagencies estirhate it may reach a total\nof 9,000,000 within a few months.\n\u201cThe A'merican Federation of Labor\nis fearful that unemployment may be\ncome even more serious than anyone\nanticipates and that it may extend\nlonger than can be risked with safety\nto the nation.\n\u201cOur country is shockingly unpre\npared to meet this crisis.\n\u201cThe Executive Council of the Amer\nican Federation of Labor wishes to em\nphasize the tremendous importance of\nswift and effective action. The govern\nment must reach new heights of leader\nship. Reconversion must be given the\ngreen light,\n\u201cThere is evidence of delay and pro\ncrastination by government agencies\nin dealing with reconversion problems.\nA new spirit an4 a new policy must be\ninvoked.\u201d 1\nIn a formal statement the Executive,\nCouncil before adjourning its summer\nsession, expressed labor\u2019s joy in victory\nand its fears as to the future. The\nstatement conducted:\n\u201cCongress should move at once to\nprovide for human needs during recon\nversion and to take such measures as\nwill encourage and aid private indus\ntry to expand production and provide\njobs for all within a reasonable period.\n\u201cFor its own part, the American Fed\neration of Labor believes that organ\nized labor has an important contribu\ntion to make to the postwar recovery\n.program. _\n\u201cThe advent of critical and trouble\nsome'industrial problems'is certain vto\ncause widespread, unrest. Disturbances\nin industrial relations caused by the\nsudden impact of peace must not be al\nlowed to get out of hand. America still\nhas a vitally important job to do\u2014to\nwin the peace 1\u201d\nMr. Green announced that the Ex\necutive Council expected President\nTruman to issue a call for a postwar\nlabor-industry conference for the pur\npose of maintaining stable labor rela\ntions and preventing strikes. i\nThe Executive Council, he said,\nagreed that the American Federation\nof Labor would participate in such a\nconference when called.\nIt was recalled that the War Labor\nBoard was set up as a result of the\nlabor-industry conference called by\nPresident Roosevelt shortly after Pearl\nHarbor.\nThe purposes of the new conference\nwill be to reach agreement on a setup\nj to provide for the disposition of thou\nsands of pending cases now awaiting\ndecision by the WLB and the develop\nment of facilities by which new indus\ntrial problems can be settled under the\nWage Stabilization Act of 1942, which\ndocs not expire until six months after\nFascist Plots\n(Continued from Page One)\nwas enclosed in an envelope with the\naddress'of' Walker\u2019s organization and\nwas accompanied by a begging letter 1\nsigned by Walker. _ v\nThis memorandum revealed how\nthe CIO was to be accused of being\n\u201ccommunistic and atheistic.\u201d A\nscheme was divulged to seek a writ\nof mandamus, under which scuiyilons\ncharges could be made .against the\nCIO without fear of being prosecuted'*,\nunder the libel laws.\nPublications of an inflammatory hg\nture were to be circulated, falsely pur\nporting to be issued by the CIO itself. t\nWorld War II veterans were to t\u00bbe\nrecruited on the basis of toughness\nand \u201cpeculiar abilities\u201d to take violent\naction against the CIO- V\nCIO members were to be trapped\non the basis of understandings with\ncertain police officers. s\nNewspapers which refused to jotn\nin the Fight for Free Enterprise cam\npaign were to be disciplined by circu\nlation and advertising boycotts.\nIn placing proof of their charges\nbefore Attorney General Sellers,\nKnight and Akin asked him to in;\nvestigate Fight for Free Enterprise,\nto revoke its charter and to prosecute\nWalker and his associates.\nVA\n'.O\u2019.i'. v. ':;p^ y\\ :;:-V ?v :.M\nThe\n\u2022.